The digital platform for employee social engagement

     Alaya is the social engagement platform that allows thousands of
     individuals, brands and companies to do their part and act upon the
     social and environmental challenges of this century while building a
     positive culture at work.

How it works ?

   Choose an association. Choose how you want to help. Do your part.

Skills-based Volunteering

   Our knowledge is our most precious asset. Share it with associations
   that need it and help them boost their impact.

Field Volunteering

   Alone or as a team, organise volunteering days in the field to support
   the project and cause of your choice.

Donations

   Create an internal fundraising campaign. Contribute to the philanthropy
   of your company. Simply make a donation.

Goods Collections

   Do not throw things away, recycle. Office materials, medical devices,
   toys for Christmas. Organise it easily.

   More information

They trust Alaya

   They have implemented a powerful social tech initiative and we are very
   proud to support them.

   As the manager of a small consulting firm, I am convinced of the
   importance of the company's social role. Despite the alignment of our
   program with our vision, administrative barriers have hindered our
   ability to achieve our objectives. Alaya is perfectly suited - offering
   excellent services to encourage, manage and promote solidarity
   engagement!
   Jean-François Saint-Pierre
   Jean-François Saint-PierreCEO Evolusys

   We feel that people want to have an impact, do something real, make
   sense, want to help and get involved. When you work in banking,
   insurance, IT or any other sector, it can become a challenge. Alaya
   offers us a solution.
   Jürgen Müller
   Jürgen Müller Partner PwC

   Creating a link and structuring a commitment strategy for its employees
   is Alaya's strength. A real accelerator for companies that want to
   strengthen their employee engagement policy and community practice.
   Jonathan Normand
   Jonathan NormandDirecteur exécutif B Lab (Suisse)

   Alaya is a strong example of a social-tech company that seeks to boost
   social impact through innovative technological solutions. In this
   context, the newly launched IIS by EPFL aims to link technology and
   innovation to maximize social impact and become an accelerator for
   social-tech companies like Alaya that combine profit and impact.
   Beatrice Scarioni
   Beatrice ScarioniSocial Impact Initiative (SII) - EPFL
